article.headline: Oklahoma St. 104, Mercer 74
article.story: STILLWATER, Okla. -- James Anderson led six players in double figures with 20 points as Oklahoma State beat Mercer 104-74 on Wednesday in the Cowboys' first home game in 25 days. Oklahoma State (7-3) hadn't played at Gallagher-Iba Arena since Nov. 23 after opening the season with four home games. Anderson, Obi Muonelo (19), Terrel Harris (18), Keiton Page (13), Byron Eaton (12) and Malcoln Kirkland (10) each scored in double figures for the Cowboys. Junior guard James Florence led Mercer (6-4) with 27 points. The game was a homecoming of sorts for Mercer head coach Bob Hoffman, an Oklahoma native who coached the women's team at Southern Nazarene and the men's squad at Oklahoma Baptist before working as an assistant at Oklahoma. Anderson made six 3-pointers, tying his career high, in eight attempts from behind the arc.
